    "body": "### Problem\n\nWith ui2 enabled, the ruler of a floating window is not cleared after leaving its window; the stale ruler persists in the command-line area.\n\n`<C-L>` temporarily clears it, but returns when the cursor is moved.  \nEntering and leaving the command-line seems to properly clear it, though.\n\nAppears to only happen when `'rulerformat'` is set. (the vanilla ruler is unaffected?)\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\nrequire('vim._extui').enable { enable = true }\nvim.o.rulerformat = '%l %c %{win_gettype()}'\nvim.api.nvim_open_win(0, false, { relative = 'editor', row = 1, col = 1, width = 10, height = 10 })\nvim.api.nvim_input '<c-w>w<c-w>p'\n```\n\nNote that the ruler of the float continues to show in the cmdline (`0 0 popup`) even when moving the cursor in the main split window.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nRuler in the command-line area should be cleared after leaving the float (I guess more specifically, when entering a window that has a statusline), like when `'rulerformat'` is _not_ set.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-2159+g28c294363f\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nFedora 43 Workstation\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nghostty 1.2.3, tmux 3.5a\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nSource",
